&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;h2&gt;The Company You’ll Join&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Carta connects founders, investors, and limited partners through world-class software, purpose-built for everyone in venture capital, private equity and private credit. Trusted by 65,000+ companies in 160+ countries, Carta’s platform of software and services lays the groundwork so you can build, invest, and scale with confidence.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Carta’s Fund Administration platform supports 9,000+ funds and SPVs, representing nearly $185B in assets under management, with tools designed to enhance the strategic impact of fund CFOs. Recognized by Fortune, Forbes, Fast Company, Inc. and Great Places to Work, Carta is shaping the future of private market infrastructure.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Together, Carta is creating the end-to-end ERP platform for private markets. Traditional ERP solutions don’t work for Private Funds. Private capital markets need a comprehensive software solution to replace outdated spreadsheets and fragmented service providers. Carta’s software for the Office of the Fund CFO does just that - it’s a new category of software to make private markets look more like public markets - a connected ERP for private capital.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For more information about our offices and culture, check out our &lt;a href=&quot;https://carta.com/careers/&quot;&gt;Carta careers page&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2&gt;The Team You’ll Work With&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The GTM Strategy &amp;amp; Operations team partners with Sales &amp;amp; Marketing leaders to drive Carta’s revenue strategy and best-in-class execution. This role is a critical hire for the AMEA (APAC, Middle East, and Africa) team, supporting a region to scale across private markets ecosystem.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be the operational backbone for our AMEA GTM leaders, working closely with an expanding team of Sales and Marketing partners. You will also serve as the primary strategic bridge between regional requirements and our Global RevOps teams to build a world-class international operating model.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Problems You’ll Solve&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a GTM Strategy &amp;amp; Ops Associate, you will own the operational roadmap for the AMEA region, using process, systems, and data as levers to accelerate productivity. You will solve complex problems as we move into different asset classes and complex sales motions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strategic Territory &amp;amp; Execution: Own AMEA territory planning, account segmentation, and Book of Business assignments to ensure equitable coverage and maximum sales velocity.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Data &amp;amp; Analytics Foundation: Own business requirements for regional reporting. Create and maintain BI dashboards that proactively identify risks and opportunities in the AMEA pipeline and customer retention.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Process Architect: Design and implement &quot;Lead-to-Cash&quot; workflows for new asset classes and complex GTM motions (e.g., ERP integrations). Conduct User Acceptance Testing (UAT) for tool releases and system improvements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Global Bridge: Collaborate with US RevOps, Systems and Data teams to ensure the AMEA roadmap is codified within global data architecture. Localize global policies while ensuring regional nuances (multi-currency, local regulations) are supported.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Tech Stack Management: Manage and optimize regional tools (SFDC, LeanData, Outreach, Chorus, Marketo etc.) to drive automation and ensure data hygiene.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strategic Advisory: Serve as a trusted advisor to AMEA GTM leadership, providing data-driven insights for QBRs, board materials, and executive analyses.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About You&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate is a proactive, mid-level operator who thrives in high-growth, ambiguous environments and is comfortable balancing high-level strategy with &quot;hands-on&quot; systems execution.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience: 5+ years of experience in GTM Operations, Sales Strategy, or Revenue Operations, preferably within an Enterprise SaaS environment. Experience in Venture Capital, Private Equity or related Private Capital Markets is encouraged.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analytical Power: Highly proficient in SQL and BI tools (Metabase). You know how to translate complex data into meaningful insights for executive leadership.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Systems Expert: Advanced proficiency in Salesforce (SFDC). Familiarity with the GTM tech stack (e.g., LeanData, Outreach, Marketo, SQL, GSuite).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Owner Mentality: You take pride in building from the ground up. You are a self-starter who can operate independently while influencing cross-functional stakeholders at all levels.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Global Perspective: Experience or interest in international markets; ability to navigate and communicate effectively across time zones and diverse regional requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Structured Thinker: Exceptional ability to frame business questions with data and implement actionable process improvements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Disclosures:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We are an equal opportunity employer and are committed to providing a positive interview experience for every candidate. If accommodations due to a disability or medical condition are needed, please connect with the talent partner via email.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Carta uses E-Verify in the United States for employment authorization. See the &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.e-verify.gov/about-e-verify/what-is-e-verify&quot;&gt;E-Verify&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;Department&quot;&gt;Department of Justice&lt;/a&gt; websites for more details.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;For information on our data privacy policies, see&amp;nbsp;&lt;a class=&quot;c-link&quot; href=&quot;https://carta.com/privacy/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; data-stringify-link=&quot;https://carta.com/privacy/&quot; data-sk=&quot;tooltip_parent&quot;&gt;Privacy&lt;/a&gt;,&amp;nbsp;&lt;a class=&quot;c-link&quot; href=&quot;https://carta.com/privacy/candidate/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; data-stringify-link=&quot;https://carta.com/privacy/candidate/&quot; data-sk=&quot;tooltip_parent&quot;&gt;CA Candidate Privacy&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a class=&quot;c-link&quot; href=&quot;https://carta.com/legal/br/brazil-pay-transparency/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; data-stringify-link=&quot;https://carta.com/legal/br/brazil-pay-transparency/&quot; data-sk=&quot;tooltip_parent&quot;&gt;Brazil Transparency Report&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Please note that all official communications from us will come from an @carta.com or @carta-external.com domain. Report any contact from unapproved domains to security@carta.com.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
